"0#Looking both ways|We've got less days ahead of us than behind us on the journey to Workhuman Live Online. But there's no coasting downhill for this team. Some of the work is ramping up, some of it is continuing to speed along. You've all been putting forth your best efforts,  and many extra hours. The shared experiences build not only the event but also keeps the department strong. Cheers to you!\n\n1#Thank You for Everything|Matt - Thank you for giving me a chance here at Workhuman, for giving me the runway to figure out my way around the Marketing organization, and for being a person to always bounce ideas off. This is the best job I've ever had, and you're a huge reason why. I know I can speak for the other members of the team when I say that your thoughtful and consistent leadership helped us be as successful as we have been. You're going to do such great things at your new company, and they're getting an amazing person to help bring them to the next level. I'm trying not to sound too redundant, but thank you so much for everything. I wish you nothing but the best moving forward.\n\n2#Taking the lead!|Just wanted to thank you for all of your help and leadership since my transition to your team. You're super responsive and very understanding of the frustrations that arise day-to-day. Thank you for your help and guidance!\n\n3#Online and On Point|Matt, Jon, Jeff - Thank you for your quick work this week to make sure our WHL Online registrants have a terrific and consistent experience regardless of which website property they engage with. I am very excited about the overall look and feel of the sites! With gratitude, -C\n\n4#Virtual Offsite - but 100% Productive IRL|Team - On behalf of Patti and myself thank you for a tremendous Q3 strategic planning and execution offsite last week. Both presenters and discussion partners excelled in their roles to communicate and strengthen existing plans. Your engagement and participation was locked in for the full session. And it's exciting to see this team rally around a new way of working that is oriented toward connecting business results to the strategic objectives of all our 2H initiatives within Marketing and across partner stakeholder teams. Thanks for leaning into the process - it's becoming a difference maker for us and helping us cut through our own noise! -C\n\n5#Thanks for the Google Analytics tour!|Matt, I wanted to thank you for all of your help over the past month. I reached out regarding some possible reporting tools for our new certification/customer sites and you offered to help get me set up in Google Analytics for much better reporting. Not only that, you took time out of your day to give me a detailed walkthrough of the GA portal to learn about the different types of reporting and where to find them. This tool will be a great help as we launch the certified professional site, and it will help us find the most popular pieces of communication that customers are accessing in our Customer Center. Thanks again!\n\n6#Partnering on Technology Procurement|Matt, thank you for all of your support over the last few weeks on new procurement projects and renewals. You have been so open and enthusiastic about working together, embracing our involvement, and taking the time to explain each software package you are considering. It has been great learning about a new area in Workhuman and I’ve really enjoyed working with you.  Thanks again, looking forward to working closer together in the future.\n\n7#Measurement for success|A bit late but I wanted to thank you all for your dedication, collaboration, and teamwork as we solidified measurements for Awareness, Perception and Preference. Learning and listening to each other through every meeting, I saw such great passion for accuracy and full transparency in the unknown. We worked together to present solid recommendations, and received great feedback. With our next steps to operationalize, use Q1-Q2 2020 as litmus on measurements, and prepare for QBRs together we'll create the best measurable Brand marketing we've ever had. I couldn't be more proud of this team.\n\n8#Negotiation Dream Team|Thomasina, Niall and Matt, thank you so much for all of your help and guidance navigating the Sendoso contract revisions. Each of you carefully helped to create a well thought out plan to get clauses written for us around quality, SLAs and even stability into one constructive conversation. The explanation to Sendoso's team went so smoothly it appears that we will be able to get everything included as a part of the new contract. Thank you again for all of the hard work and I truly appreciate the teamwork!!\n\n9#Trusting the process!|Team - thank you for buying into and committing to the new process and approach we're using to develop an integrated and collaborative 2H Marketing Plan (ie., offsite, collaboration, data-driven goal setting, etc.). Because of your willingness to lean into this new way of working we've been able to advance new creative, powerful, innovative ideas for 2H digital programming, virtual engagements, and WHL-S that tap into the zeitgeist, create urgency, represent that Companies that thrive Workhuman, in a way that is unique to our Brand and business. With gratitude, Chris & Patti\n\n10#Pioneers Unite!|Team - Thank you for your unyielding focus and energy in our \"first ever\" digital planning session for 2H '20 and Oct WHL-S initiatives. This was an epic-ly long virtual offsite that uncovered and unlocked critical new and innovative thinking for representing our solutions as \"essential\" and \"compelling\". Thank you for 100% commitment to this session and the ensuing outcomes. Lots of powerful thinking and actionable next steps to fuel our high growth, marketing making, and bleeding edge tech company and brand. With gratitude,  -C\n\n11#The future is now. The future is working human.|Team - this group has been the nucleus for \"what's next.\" You've ripped up and thrown away the rule book for what was. You've embraced the freedom, liberation and inspiration that comes from having a blank sheet of paper to operate from. Yes, we've been grinding the last two weeks, but we are on the precipices of exciting concepts that will propel our brand and business forward. Keep pushing, we're nearly there. With gratitude, -C\n\n12#All in a day's work|THIS. TEAM. Day in and day out, you rally to turn around quick requests when necessary. You challenge each other to make our processes smoother and more efficient. You ask the difficult questions. You take the time and create the head space to stop, reflect, analyze and propose new ideas. Even when it's stressful or dare I say, frustrating for reasons sometimes out of our immediate control, you stay engaged and focused on the end game. Ever committed to evolving our digital experiences in big and small ways because we all understand there's never a silver bullet. It's a combination of MANY efforts that will ultimately lead us where we want to go. I value your vast talents, strong work ethic, sense of humor, and most of all, the true partnership this web team has cultivated even while being physically apart for the last three months....and I remain ever so grateful for all that you do in a day's work. Thank you for making us better in more ways than one.\n\n13#SEO Wins!|As a result of your hard work and incredible skills with our SEO, we're seeing some great inbound activity. Just this week in PR activity we had one journalist (from the WSJ!) reach out because of Eric's video and one article published that referenced Workhuman insight from 2019. All the work you're doing to keep Workhuman in front of people is really paying off - thank you!\n\n14#What Makes Us Human: Heart and Soul|Team, when most of us are feeling defeated, deflated, and hopeless, each of you came together to unite our hearts and souls with the people we most want to reach. I shed more than one tear experiencing the imagery and messages of hope and pragmatism. Your respect, empathy, and compassion for all hearts and souls inside and outside of our company has made an impact.  Thank you for transforming a sad exception to our lives into one that brings us together instead of dividing us all.  As always, thank you for your hard work and determination to Workhuman. Best, Patti\n\n15#An Amazing welcome|I just wanted to thank everyone for an amazing welcoming to the team. You guys have managed to create a lot of excitement for me. I cannot wait to get involved in all the different projects and good times we have coming up ahead of us.  Thank you\n\n16#Masters of Your Universe!|Do a digital event they said.  Do it in a month, too.  With lots of video, and new tech integrations, and a massive simultaneous user load.  And oh yeah – keep all those other web project rolling along at the same time.  You know, a product launch, and COVID content, and a Healthcare campaign.  We basically tossed 3 months worth of work at you guys to tackle in just weeks – and you stepped up like never before.  From weekend work, to live editing, to solution creation, and perhaps even some impressive crisis management that really saved the day.  We couldn’t have pulled of what we did without you both behind the scenes.  Your ability to remain calm, focused, and take immediate action is invaluable.  It brings a sense of relief knowing that your on the team and always ready to do your part and more.  Thank you for all you do, and all you did!\n\n17#Resources Ninja!|Matty, thank you so much for your quick work when I asked if you could help us create an Uberflip stream for a customer communication! This content will be invaluable for our customers as they navigate through this next phase of work. I'm so happy we could curate this quickly and offer it up to this group. Helps us continue to be seen as a thought leader and an advocate for our valued customers. Very much appreciate the support!\n\n18#Fierce commitment to urgency|\"We are now faced with the fact that tomorrow is today. We are confronted with the fierce urgency of now. In this unfolding conundrum of life and history, there IS such a thing as being too late. This is not time for apathy or complacency. This is a time for vigorous and positive action.\" - MLK JR.   Team, since I started just over a month ago, I have heard from many of you and our stakeholders who have talked about the misfortune of joining Workhuman during a global pandemic that has changed every thing about how we live: from how we interact, to what we spend our time and money on, what we value, and how we work.  The truth is, there was no better time for me to be able to witness the magic that is Workhuman. We already know what is important and that is human connection. What you have demonstrated is humanity during a time of extreme urgency - a rarity in life and certainly in business. Thank you for your passion for your and your commitment to each other and our stakeholders.  I am honored to work alongside each of you.\n\n19#Moodtracker Launch success!|Team – Thank you for delivering our brand new Moodtracker product. Thank you so much to everybody for the amazing work on the Moodtracker product. Hard to believe this was just an idea at the beginning of January. Since then a team has formed, the product designed, architected, built, tested, branded, communicated, marketed and launched. Whew. The speed at which the groups collaborated is a tribute to the sense of camaraderie and positivity we have at Workhuman. The energy, imagination has shone through in every way. This coupled with the determination to deliver a world-class product means that today we have a sixth edition to our Workhuman Cloud suite. Welcome Moodtracker. On behalf of all of the humans in the company, thank you. Eric.\n\n20#Command Central|Thank you all for making yourselves available on the zoom call for the entire length of the WHL Stream event. Having all of us connected was instrumental in our ability to respond quickly and swiftly when we were met with unseeable adversity. We were able to give real time analytics, statistics, and updates on communications throughout the course of the event. Once things settled down we were even able to share a laugh or too (I think you smiled at least once, right Matt?). In a time where we couldn’t be huddled together in the same room, it really didn’t feel like we were all that apart.\n\n21#Strike Team Web Rides Again!|What an amazing couple of weeks for this team! On top of a huge technical challenge for Workhuman Livestream you created multiple new websites and updates to support the Moodtracker launch and Workhuman Livestream post-event strategy. Jon, not sure how you pulled off building so much high quality web content (although judging by the amount of late night/weekend discussions we had I have a guess!) Geoff, great work pulling together multiple unique homepage updates on top of multiple demos, critical to driving the business. Nick, as always you guide what we do from an SEO perspective, but your role doesn’t end there. You provide sound strategy as well as eagle eyes when it comes to QA (not sure how we all missed the report on that phone image!) Finally Matt, you lead this motley band of web warriors on successful launch after successful launch, and you’ve been on top of your game for countless weeks without missing a beat. Great work everyone!\n\n22#43 slacks in 19 minutes - that's some data|Yes, that's what you did together. Members of the whl-stream-tech channel - between 1:00 and 1:19 you urgently yet calmly worked together to troubleshoot, problem solve, implement, and communicate a workaround. I was watching you. You saved the day because you worked together and responded decisively. Sweat and tears, and a whole lot of teamwork.  Not to imply there were not many backup plans and scenarios discussed in advance because there was no shortage of that. But when the moment came, decisions needed to be made, action needed to be taken... and you did all that. Kudos.\n\n23#Keeping Humanity Alive with Live!|Team – Thank you for delivering a high quality, compelling, on brand, and “of the moment” digital event. In less than six weeks you expertly pivoted from the cancellation of our physical events in San Antonio and Dublin and leaped into bold new thinking that resulted in our Workhuman Live Stream event. You were fearless in pursuit of our audacious goal of 10,000 registrants and charged furiously at it – obliterating the goal and achieving more than 15,000+ registrants. This level of success took thoughtful planning, decisive and quick action, creativity, and relentless outreach to secure exceptional guest speakers, high profile customer stories, and new sponsorships. There was clear demonstration of teamwork, resilience, grit – and quite a bit of “good cheer” across this group. It was an example of Workhuman at our best. This is a significant achievement in the company’s history and will continue to pay dividends in the following areas: Social reach; The launch of our new products like Moodtracker; Deepening existing customer relationships; Establishing strong new footholds with future customers; And growing profitably. My hat’s off to you all – when Humanity needed us most – you all rallied to give Humanity the company it needed now more than ever. On behalf of the Leadership Team and myself, Thank you - Eric\n\n24#Web team warriors|Thank you for continuing to be the most awesome web team ever....We're seven weeks into this WFH journey and I remain in awe of each of you for your consistent level of engagement, creativity and quality of work - even when things are being thrown at you left and right and needed in a heartbeat. I am grateful for you and enjoy the connections we have formed with each other. As each day passes, i can feel them strengthening and that is a very good thing.\n\n25#Fantastic Playbook Development Workshop|Thank you all so much for taking big chunks of your time over the last two days to participate in the playbook development workshop. We are tackling all of the important pieces as we continue to redesign Workhuman's demand generation and account based marketing, ensuring that we're focused on the right future customers, delivering the most important messages at each stage of the journey, and arming our teams with the right training and tools to develop more opportunities and win more deals. The experience, energy, enthusiasm, and creative thinking over the last two days was phenomenal; and I can't wait to bring it to life in the new playbook. I'm very grateful for the outstanding collaboration and commitment to sales and marketing alignment!\n\n26#Questions & Answers = Crushing it|The questions were: \"Are you there?\" \"You working?\" \"Can you come inside on this beautiful Sunday?\" The answers from this group were \"Yes!\" \"How can I help?\" \"Be right there!\"  Thank your dedication, time out of your weekend (or your whole weekend), and flexibility. For answering your phone, responding to texts, jumping on calls, endless Slacks, and using Workfront ;-)  Multiple communication channels are needed to launch a promotional campaign in 4 days, over a weekend, while working remotely. I am proud of you, to be a part of this team, and for what we accomplished together. Thank you.\n\n27#Livestream Launch!|I was going to find an image of a nice stream for this recognition, but the way this team came together and launched – with immediate results (more on that below) – a rocket made more sense.  We have been in a hurry up and wait, start and stop process on bringing a digital/live stream event to market for a bit now.  In the past few weeks it all started to come together, and this past weekend it all really came together.  Our band of weekend warriors once again rallied to pull everything into place and then dragged many more souls into the battle for a rapid Monday launch.  With Dianne at the helm providing impeccable project management and, might I say, a few beatings we were all kept on task.  Jen, Chris, Kevin, and Jay – you were right there every step of the way on design iterations and animations.  Owen, you’ve been a master of the nuanced wordsmithing we’ve needed on this.  Matt, Biz, Geoff and Mark – you built, staged, tested, and launched all new site pages and elements in almost no time at all.  Your work set-up for a great launch – where we dragged in Anthony to build, test, and deploy our emails with about an hours time from asset to release.  Rob and Roshni jumped in to iterate social/digital and bring us live globally.  Colleen, Anne and Jess pulled the enablement tools and comms together and put them in everyone’s hands to help us all share and promote the program.  Mike and Lauren working the external networks to amplify and extend reach.  And Jill.  Maintaining a calm presence, helping align priorities and strategy, and ensuring we’re on track for the overall business goal.  We’re really just a the start of a 3-week journey.  Much work is yet to be done, but you put us in the best possible place to succeed.  So much so, that within hours of launching, we already over 1000 registrants.  Impressive!  I so enjoy working with this team and knowing that together – we can and will deliver!\n\n28#Running apart - So we can run together|Workhuman runners club! ... 'Sup?!  Thank you for keeping together the community that running offers us. Even though we have to run solo these days, and even wear masks (ya, you try doing that) when running, you've kept me resilient in something that is of great importance to me (even greater now) and brings me strength and mindfulness when I need it most. I appreciate the creativity and camaraderie the \"virtual\" challenges we have concocted bring us.  Though I am never at risk of \"winning\" these, the shear knowledge of knowing we're out there \"apart\" but \"together\" is heartening. Keep running, as we still have \"miles to go\"! With gratitude, -C\n\n29#Are you there?|Yea you were! Thank you, Matt, for joining a website meeting with negative notice. You jumped on the call, read a few notes and contributed to the conversation to support your team. Way to lead and be a teammate. I appreciate your dedication.\n\n30#Thank You Healthcare Images - Weekend Worriors|Thank you all for jumping in to take part in the logo and image sourcing and uploading for hospitals into the Thank You Healthcare site!  Ensuring that the experience is personal and meaningful for those who access the site is incredibly important and your help in making this happen was invaluable! I got to see first-hand your passion, collaboration and sheer energy brought to this exciting task!  You gave up time over your Easter weekend with family to dedicate energy toward this grand human cause.  Adam, Becky and Meghan, thank you for leading the cross functional team from activating help from across the company, providing detailed instructions (that even I could follow), guidance, direction, answering questions and providing top tips and learnings throughout the process, even participating as heavy hitters in the uploading and sourcing as well! When I asked you, Becky and Meg, to help partner with Adam and the technology team to make this happen you were so excited to be a part of this phenomenal project and your pride was palpable- thank you!  You guys have become the 3 amigos!  Superb effort, and excellent management, your incredible knowledge and attention to detail has been awe-inspiring! Thank you also to each of you who dedicated an hour, several hours and in some cases most of the weekend to sourcing and uploading!  We so appreciate your efforts!  Many hands make light work, my mother used to say! I do want to call out a few of you who really made an incredible dent in the project uploading and sourcing between 70 and 230 images each and in many cases hitting both uploading and sourcing!  WOW!  Brian Moore, Matt Durgin, John Wamback, Jon Bizeur, Amanda Salvas, Rich Sorrentino, Jillian Gregoriou and Dan Fiore, you guys are complete rock stars and your contributions were mammoth! This was a true team effort and to see it in action makes me so proud to be a part of our Workhuman family!  Amazing job! Let’s share some gratitude with the world now!\n\n31#Leading by example|Matt - Thank you for continuing to keep your teams wellbeing at top of mind and calling out when someone took advantage of an opportunity to spend time with their family. It’s so important to  make sure your team is balancing work and life. Keep it up!\n\n32#Engage warp factor.....10|I Wanted to take a moment to show some gratitude for my amazing team. I am constantly impressed with the teams ability to respond to digital challenges and new initiatives with a sense of urgency and agility. The past couple weeks have been fast paced with changes to the website and our resources section.  Even moving at light speed everyone makes it a point to embrace all ideas and perspectives as well as support each other. With that type of collaboration and cohesiveness great things are able to be accomplished. Congrats on the launch this week!  It is a pleasure working with you all. In the words of a famous starship captain \"Things are only impossible until they're not\" ― Jean-Luc Picard\n\n33#We're putting the band back together|As a former web-guy I can’t express how much I’ve enjoyed working with this team again on a daily basis throughout the past two weeks. In many ways it's felt like a reunion with multiple iterations of the Workhuman Web Team working together once again!   Jon and Geoff, it’s been incredible watching the progress you’ve made on all of our web properties. You’ve been raising the bar not by the day or even the hour, but often by the minute, responding to the current need with an agile thinking and execution (sorry, I had to say it!).   Nick, you’ve quickly become a north star for strategic thinking on this team. Your thoughtful approach to every challenge, and ability to take the lead, especially on our resources page is beyond impressive.   And finally, Matt, it’s been an absolute pleasure getting the chance work with you again in a rapid development situation. It’s amazing how much our two man web operation, once focused on developing new websites has transformed into a fully-fledged digital strategy powerhouse.  I’m truly excited to see how the evolution we’re seeing on all of our digital properties continues in the coming year. There is a desire beyond the current situation with Covid-19 for relevant content that works in synergy with all of marketing’s campaigns and beyond. Keep up this amazing work!\n\n34#8:45am - sunshine and smiles!|This week has been an amazing opportunity for us three to connect on a level like never before. Every morning, 8:45am, I'm greeted with sunshine and smiles from you both. Me eating my cereal, us talking about the night before and the day ahead, I've loved our banter, our camaraderie, and our candor. Together, we are a great team and by the floods of recognition for your team members, your leadership is speaking louder than words. I'm incredibly proud of you both. Hope you have an incredible weekend and I'll see you bright and early on Monday 8:45am!\n\n35#Hidden Talents|We all have been working hard on some face paced projects that have had some real impact - it has been a whirlwind few weeks! One of my favorite parts about this group dynamic is that we aren’t afraid to offer up new ideas and try new ways of thinking. Everyday we learn about hidden skills that each one of us can summon to help the team move even faster and make the projects run smoother. Whether or not our suggestions make it to the final iteration is irrelevant - we are all working to achieve the same goal and support and help each other immensely along the way.  We call our daily chat a “safe space” and I genuinely believe it is. We aren't afraid to challenge each other, laugh, and grow together. It is an honor to work with a group of such talented (and hidden talented) people such as yourselves. This team is a powerhouse and I’m excited for what comes next!\n\n36#triple threat|This recognition is seriously overdue so I'm SHOUTING FROM THE ROOFTOPS (social distancing approved) how thankful I am for you Matt.  You're an anomaly;  a triple threat if you will.  Strategy.  Technology.  Execution.  Very few leaders can master all 3 skills; but not you my friend.  You look at a challenge from 360°, understand the role of technology and move forward with purpose.  I'm consistently in awe of your ability to take on a project from start to finish so thoughtfully - even as a new PAWRENT!  I have so much respect for your work ethic and want you to know how appreciative I am of YOU (bold, italics, underline!).\n\n37#It was a moment!|A huge and sincere T H A N K Y O U to this long list of amazing humans. It seems like an eternity but just a short few weeks ago at the Executive off-site down in Florida, Eric and his team were all seated for a session. Each person was handed a sealed envelope with their name on it. Inside were the private letters each of you wrote. Some vulnerable, some filled with humor but all filled with how that person made you feel. It was a moment! Silence, smiles and even tears. It's not every day you get the chance to silence an entire Executive Team and remind them of how much they also matter and how they have influenced your day, week - or career. Thank you for being at the heart of what made this moment come to life.You all are amazing!  -Rebecca & Alice\n\n38#What a Year This Week has Been|Brian, Matt, and Z -  *exhales* ok so that was a whirlwind. We hit the ground running at about 100 MPH this week and didn't (at the time of me writing this, we still haven't) stop once. Our team kept pushing forward and we turned around an incredible product. None of that would have been possible without the three of you. You all formed a cohesive management team that not only kept us updated and on track, but you all went to bat for us too and that means so much. A lot of what happens on the backend goes unseen so to have you all as voices for the team was instrumental in pushing Phase 1 across the finish line (and presumably Phase 2 by the time you read this). Looking at this week as the most stressful of stress tests, I know that we have a kick ass team that is going to crush any project that comes our way.\n\n39#More like: Page Under Reinvention!|Team - Incredible lift today to align our core website property with burning platform initiatives. We now are in position to drive all humans to an ever-evolving, ever-improving web platform. This creates immediate value today and will continue to pay dividends as we drive more traffic from more initiatives to Workhuman.com. Thank you for mobilizing asap and driving significant improvements in the past 24 hours. Well done and great demonstration of the behaviors and teamwork we need to harness this moment for the company and our customers. With gratitude, -C\n\n40#Is this what Brian means by agile?|Wanted to give a quick shout out to this team for all the great thinking and ACTION around updating our site to respond to the current times. The sense of urgency is super high, the direction keeps changing, we're all remote and trying to keep up and learn how best to work together but you guys continue to amaze me with your responsiveness, resourcefulness and flexibility. I hope this is the first of many collaborations we'll have together! I am beyond grateful for your partnership, creativity and commitment to getting sh*t done! Thank you!!\n\n41#Team Corona|Coronavirus.  Covid-19.  A giant headache.  We all call it something different – especially because the situation with it has been changing minute by minute and making our decision making process so challenging.  When we made the decision to create new content and FAQ’s for our Workhuman Live site and audiences at 8PM on a Friday night, I crossed my fingers we would be able to activate.  We needed to get information out to our audiences that was clear, consistent, and valuable to ensure they felt informed and at ease.  No surprise – every single one of you stepped up.  Dianne was slacking me almost immediately with project set-up details and timelines.  Lauren had copy in my hands before 6:00 AM (you actually sent it at 1:30!?!)  Chris and Amy were both there to review, edit and get on the phone to talk it through.  Jon had site pages staged and new pop-up functionality built and staged Saturday morning.  Jen and Anthony had layouts and content ready to deploy.  Jill was providing copy strategy and reviews.  Holly and Anne were standing by ready to act as needed for our audiences.  And Lauren – our guiding light and champion of strategy supporting the whole process was as responsive as ever with reviews and feedback.  This is such an evolving and fluid situation, but the team never ceases to amaze me.  You gave up family and weekend time to help ensure our customers had the information they needed, when they needed it.  Your continued dedication and respect for customers, urgency, quality, and teamwork is amazing.  Thank you – and Cheers to Team Corona.\n\n42#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n43#Shoutout to all my Saucy Aunts|Thank you all so much for bringing great energy, enthusiasm, and attention to the kickoff with Influitive! This was a true cross-functional effort with representation from CX, CS, Strategy and Consulting, Marketing, Sales Operations, and Design – an awesome demonstration of the power of collaboration. As we heard, even our Influitive consultant was impressed with how much involvement we had. You all brought unique perspectives on how we can engage with and deliver value to our customers through this community platform. I’m still riding the wave of excitement coming from our kickoff and am so excited to engage with each of you further in executing on the strategy we developed together. And not only were we productive, but we got to have some fun in there too ?. I’m so grateful to work alongside each and every one of you. Looking forward to the amazing things to come!\n\n44#Sprinkling the Urgency on Sprinklr|A huge thanks to this group for their collective effort to get the Sprinklr contract properly vetted, negotiated, and signed on time to secure maximum discount on the last day of their fiscal year. It was one of our largest marketing tech purchases in recent times and we wanted to get it done properly. The future of social management and listening is bright thanks to your contributions!\n\n45#Team 12: Brainstormin' with the BEST!|I want to thank you all for such a successful brainstorm session at Ignite! It was great having people from different teams come together to share ideas. First, it was nice to be in a smaller group of humans and get to meet some new friends. And it was so fun hearing about everyone's first job - we even had a nautical theme among the group. Then we dove into the brainstorm piece and the ideas were flowing. Everyone gets an A+ for participation, too! It is not always easy to share with people you just met, but this was not a challenge at all. Thanks for letting me brainstorm with the best!\n\n46#Project Bow Tie|Pam, Jill and Matt, I just wanted to call out the wonderful job you are doing with Project Bow Tie.  Reimagining our demand generation function is daunting.  But you managed Phase 1 so smoothly and we're starting to build some real momentum now.  Not only have you navigated through those ideal customer elements seamlessly, but you have kept all stakeholders well involved, informed and excited.  This type of innovation that brings together cross-functional teams and gets them all pulling in the same direction is a great example for how we will all have to act in the coming years to continue the company's growth and innovation.  We still have a long way to go but well done so far!\n\n47#What is thy bidding|Matt, can't thank you enough for everything. Ever since taking over at the helm of the Ops team, you've been a crucial part of everything to all members of the team. To me specifically, you've been an awesome mentor, helping and guiding me through the ways of new vendor procurement and strategy with them once onboarded. You've always empowered me and gave me the confidence to keep pushing into this type of work and that is something I am immensely grateful for. Working with you is always a breeze and the way you lead this team can't be understated. You are a phenomenal human and I know you and this team will continue to crush it!\n\n48#The foot that holds up the Leaning Tower of Pisa|Anthony and Matt, over the past few weeks, I've come to you with many projects for WHCT.  We've had landing pages, email sends, ad campaigns, and general set-up questions.  Every time I have a request for you, you're answer is always \"Yes! I can help.\"  It's that positive attitude that makes it a pleasure to work with you. And, for this award, I'm grateful for all the input and best-practices you provide to the team.  You've become valuable resources for us as we build out our small business product. Thank you for your dedication to ensuring we're successful.\n\n49#2019 Year in Review|I was just completing a review of our SEO/web efforts in 2019, and I am happy to report that we made incredible strides this past year. You all made those strides happen.   Jon/Geoff, you two are the unsung heroes of our marketing organization. Since I started in May, we have undertaken several, significant, web overhauls, and the two of you saw them through flawlessly. Also, thank you for letting me bother you with all my edits to the sites.   Brian, the Workhuman Live website redesign went incredibly well and that is due to your oversight. The action plan you created kept the whole team on track. All deadlines were hit (that were in our control), and for such a large team, that's a huge success.   Sarah, thank you so much for being so open to the SEO process. The content you and your team have created is already paying dividends for us in rankings and traffic, and I know we're going to see more growth in 2020.   Matt, I don't have enough space here to thank you for everything. You gave me the runway to hit the ground running, and you were a great advocate for me in so many ways. There were several projects that you jumped in on to help out which is very much appreciated.   Here's to an even more successful 2020.\n\n50#Exhibiting the best human qualities|Anthony and Matt, over the past several weeks, the WHCT team has come to you with many requests for new ads, landing pages, and code updates. And your response every time is, \"YES!\" I'm so grateful for your positive attitude towards these requests, which I'll admit may seem mundane, repetitive, and lack reciprocation. However, you never let that bother you. You respond to these requests quickly.  Your speed and dedication allow us to implement changes on-the-fly.  Thank you for your can-do, get-stuff-done attitude.\n\n51#RecognizeThis! Overhauled|Matt, you were instrumental in getting the RecognizeThis! blog edited for our resource center. From your backing of Geoff to helping me edit (literally) hundreds of posts, you dove in to help when you didn't need to. Our SEO score is rebounding much quicker than anticipated because of your help on this.   Thank you!\n\n52#Up for the challenge|Matt- a big shout out to you as we partner together to work on templatizing demand gen emails and landing pages with LeadMD. You helped me craft better emails to the vendor since I don’t have my Marketo lingo down. You worked with us on the budget to allow for more time we discovered we needed with all the rounds of testing and revisions. You’re on top of the communications which are key at this point. Thank you, as you have been a great support to me and the team throughout this process.\n\n53#Long Overdue|Matt, this recognition is long overdue. Ever since taking over at the helm of the Ops team you've been an integral part to the growth of our whole team. Personally, you've helped me to start delving in to the world of new vendors technologies and even our own existing ones that can always be improved. On top of that you've been an awesome ear to bounce ideas and strategy off of with all these platforms and anything else that comes up. And those both don't even begin to scratch the surface of everything you do! I know I speak for the whole team when I say THANK YOU for everything you do!\n\n54#PoliteMail|Matt, I cannot thank you enough for your help leading the charge in brining PoliteMail to reality. I am no lying when I say this is something that has been slowly in the works for years. However, you got involved and within months we went from zero to 99. We're almost there and I have you to thank. This tool is going to be a great resource for the internal comms team, allowing us to see how people engage with our messages. Thank you for your persistence with this project, steering it through every step of the process with your unflappable calm