nk you so much for your quick approval on an offer today.  While you were out of the office traveling, you still made the effort to check over and approve this offer so that we can present and send it out to the candidate before the weekend!  Providing a timely responses is just another reason as to how we make our candidate experience rock - thank you!!\n\n68#Successful Kickoff|Matt - thank you so much for taking the time to walk me through your newest Marketing Automations Specialist opportunity on your team (especially on the Monday after a holiday)!  I have never recruited for a role like this, so I appreciate you walking me through the ideal candidate and their main responsibilities.  Also, thank you for diving into my LinkedIn search with me to help set me up for success!  I feel great about the movement we are already making.  Thanks so much for your time and efforts!\n\n69#The Best Demand Gen Partners!|Matt and Jill, The last few months, we've spent a lot of time together talking about how to modernize demand generation at Workhuman, and developing a new, best-in-class framework that will drive growth for our business. These conversations have been simply awesome for so many reasons but mostly because of our partnership. We listen to each other, challenge each other, respect each other, and make each other laugh :); and the result is a smart, strategic proposal that we are proud of and excited about.  I love that we leave these meetings fired up and always say how much we love these discussions! I know this is early days of the journey, and I'm grateful to be working with you from start to finish on this. Thank you for being the best demand gen partners!\n\n70#In need a new technology|Matt, thank you for your quick response to my request to use an iPhone X.  I am creating a new video our our Conversations mobile demo and the app looks and performs best on the latest technology.  When I reached out to #GlobalMarketing and saw your immediate response, I knew I was in good hands.  Your willingness to share your resources and come to the aid of team member is unparalleled.  Thank you for your help with this project.\n\n71#Agenda at a Glance|Or, agenda in a moment.  Thanks all for coming up with a great overview of the important projects happening in Marketing, with just a little notice.  It was not only great to hear about the wonderful work happening in Marketing, but to see you all present it all so beautifully.  I am grateful for the talented team of colleagues we have at the helm and in support of all of these initiatives.  Thank you!\n\n72#What a Brainstorm|There’s nothing like a three-hour meeting, sandwiched between the company meeting, a marketing vp meeting, and countless other commitments.  Yet, every one of you came with your A-Game – ready to brainstorm a whole new approach to the Workhuman Live website experience.  Thank you all for showing up focused, open-minded, and collectively in alignment on exceeding our audiences’ expectations through the site.  Reimagining a website is never easy, especially when trying to set aside what we already know to try new things.  Every one of you stepped up to share your areas of expertise and add value into the overall plan.  Your input was so valuable and is helping to frame out an exceptional site plan for 2020.\n\n73#You are on an incredible journey|I am so inspired with how you've taken your new role to the next level. In the many years since you've joined, I've never seen you so engaged, so excited, so passionate, and so positive. You are exactly where you're supposed to be. It's my genuine pleasure to support you on your path to what, I am sure, are many great successes. You are a great role model and a great leader. Well done!\n\n74#Let's talk data!|Thank you all for participating in this morning's data think tank (especially on a Friday before the long weekend!). This was an important first step in working collaboratively to unlock the power of the data each of us collect with our teams across Marketing. I was truly inspired by all of your ideas and perspectives, and there is so much potential for us to use these analytics to take the right actions to bring everything we do for Workhuman to the next level!\n\n75#Thank you for the time|Matt - Thank you so much for your time today.  I know you are very busy (especially in the afternoon prior to a long weekend).   I am excited to support you in shaping the future of operations.  The first of many meetings.  Bear with me I while I get up to speed on all things Workhuman.  Thank you for your patience and guidance.\n\n76#Optimized from the Start|In my first two weeks here, I was able to do more of my actual job than I have been in the first two weeks at previous companies and that is because of Matt. Matt let me hit the ground running by giving me all the tools I needed. He also answered the hundred (probably more) or so questions I asked him about the company, competitors, and previous work done in the SEO space. Based on the first couple weeks, I can tell that working with him is going to be a great, cooperative experience, and I am very excited for what comes next.\n\n77#Minimally Viable Presentation|MVP TEAM! WOW! What an amazing feat pulling together one of the best narratives we ever had presented at the ELT meeting today! The information flowed, they were wowed, they laughed, it showed our strengths and highlighted our successes. You ALL were integral to making this come to life, especially during the last minute crunch hours (YAY BRUINS!!!) I was so honored to re-pre-sent all that Marketing has been working on what's to come. You are a fantastic group of humans, so grateful to work with you.\n\n78#The Master of Google Analytics|Matt, thank you so much for giving me a tutorial on Google Analytics! I had a baseline understanding but now I feel much more empowered to dig in. I also appreciate the extra time you took to help me with the WH follow-up reporting using GA. The insig