k you enough for that!\n\n87#The NUMBERS|Thank you for not only all the work you have put into the marketing efforts for the event, but the analysis and reporting as well.  It has been disappointing to see the drop of the last few weeks, but at least we have good reporting and an ability to assess things for the future.  I am grateful to have you supporting our digital efforts.\n\n88#My superhero|Matt - today I was suddenly without a computer (left it in car wife took) and needed to publish the latest Workhuman Radio. I reached out to you, hoping that you would be there, and you were! Thanks for dropping everything to help me get that up and running. You are always willing to help. Thanks!\n\n89#Late Night Launch Crew|Thank you both for staying up late to help launch the updated corporate website and Resources site. You both played critical roles in ironing out any final bugs and getting everything set  before we \"hit the switch\", assuring the new site was up and ready to go for the first wave of Workhuman brand announcements early on Wednesday. Let's do it again soon!\n\n90#Becoming Workhuman - Phase I achievement unlocked!|Team, I hope each and every one of you has taken a moment this week to appreciate what you have achieved. With ZERO external support (except for a couple of contractors doing \"find and replace\" logo updates, but that doesn't count) in just 45 WORKING DAYS (no joke) we have rebranded this great company Workhuman. It was beautifully handled and flawlessly executed, and you should all be so proud of your leadership and contribution to this historic moment. There's lots more to do, of course, but we have tremendous momentum, are off to an impeccable start, and I know we will finish strong.  I am grateful to be part of such an impressive team! We are living proof of the power of \"making work more human\". Thank you for all of your amazing efforts to make this happen!\n\n91#Data, Dissection, and Discovery|Matt and Brian - I’ve been watching you g