igns. The advent of Core campaigns for Recognition and Performance means we have a consistent presence using less team resources, the digital component is more thoughtful and effective and we are tuning up and optimizing wherever we can. 2019 is sure to be another big step up; thank you for the great work!\n\n97#Marketing Metrics and Analysis|I am certain that your insightful research and resulting recommendations have made a very positive impact on our audience acquisition efforts for WorkHuma19, and will allow us to spend our time and our budget more wisely.  Thank you for your enthusiasm and great ideas to help us reach goal!\n\n98#Working Human, Working Smart = Big Results!|Hey team, I wanted to acknowledge the great progress you have all made in just a few short weeks. From getting more data to better understanding registration sources and drivers, to launching an incredibly successful Cyber Monday campaign, it feels like every week the team gets savvier, more disciplined and more effective. You are a living demonstration of the power of \"working smart\" vs. just \"working hard\". I can't wait to see even more insights and intelligence as we continue to learn and optimize!\n\n99#Sharing your story|Globoinnovators - thank you for taking the time to answer my questions, and for sharing your GloboInnovation story. Your stories and comments on the process will serve as a wonderful example of what it's like to make the top 10, and to come out on top. Our hope is that your stories inspire others to submit in the Spring, and that we keep breaking company records on the number of submissions each year. Congratulations on your big win!\n\n100#Team Power|Just wanted to take a minute to recognize some team members who helped me out while I was running solo this week. Brian thanks for staying late Thanksgiving eve to wrap up loose ends before  heading out on vaca. Also for checking in with me on your vacation to see if I needed anything.  Thank you Matt for being available for any questions I had and  helping out on the blog posts. Lisa thank you for helping me keep track of projects and revisions as they were coming out of Design and into Dev and answering any questions I had. Also for working diligently with me during dev to ensure the best mobile layouts!\n\n101#Its take a village to pull off Cyber Monday!|WH Team!! Such good teamwork, hussle and creativity went into our Cyber Monday WorkHuman promotion. It literally took a village from design, web, ops, digital, third party, ops, content creation, registration and OH not to mention awesome leadership!!!! I'm thrilled with the results so far (over 100 registrants in a few days). Thanks so much to everyone involved who went the extra mile on this project, the results are a clear indicator of some good work and thoughtfulness. Let's get to the next milestone!!!!!!\n\n102#Partner in Crime!|Matt, I cannot thank you enough for the tremendous amount of support you have given the WH acquisition team. In the last few weeks, you have jumped in with SO much gusto to help us dig in and get the most of our efforts across all fronts, third parties, digital, website, the list goes on!  Your attention to detail and keen eye on the goals with a never fail \"get it done\" attitude has been exactly what we have needed.  Thrilled to be working with you on this project (and hopefully many more)!  you're the best!!!!\n\n103#GloboInnovation H2 2018 2nd Place|Congratulations on your 2nd place finish in this year's H2 GloboInnovation program with your entry of \"Employee Superpowers\". This was very well done, from the start of the presentation with the Deloitte quote to the example of trying to find a team to participate in GloboInnovation. It was a very well-constructed presentation. Any time we have an idea that leverages our secret sauce - our data - our attention is piqued. A few quotes from the judges: \"The team builder page was really nice,\" \"Adding tagging like LinkedIn was a great idea,\" \"this takes what we are doing in the performance area to the next level, adds a whole other dimension.\" What would have got you to #1 would have been if you had added in some natural language processing.  Thank you for participating and taking the extra time out of your busy schedule to work on this\n\n104#Part of the team|I wanted to take a minute after an exciting first couple weeks to say thanks to Angela , Brian and Matt.  Angela thanks for introducing me to this company and referring me for this position. My first week you were really helpful making sure I knew where I was going for meetings and taking a little time each morning to chat and make me feel comfortable when everything was new. Brian thanks for welcoming me to the team by getting me set up with my workspace, putting together a first day team lunch to meet everyone and checking in to see how onboarding was going all week.  Matt thanks for taking the time to be my onboarding buddy,  showing me around the office and getting me all the background information on the Globoforce website. Happy to be be here and already feel like part of team!\n\n105#Team Terminus|Matt - This is long overdue as an award to recognize how critical you've been to WorkHuman digital promotions lately. But specifically, I wanted to thank you for working with me to get the campaigns set up this week in Terminus. You pulled me into meetings with the vendor while you were getting up to speed and that was really helpful considering they've had some recent updates to the platform and services so it was good for me to re-learn the tool and to be able to sit with you and run through campaign set up. I learned there are now much easier ways to set up Tactics and campaigns that will save lots of time and make reporting on the back end easier as well. Thanks for being a great teammate and always willing to learn!\n\n106#So MANY bits!|Matt! This is really overdue... I just wanted to thank you for all the hard work over the past few months streamlining our digital marketing. Getting up to speed and understanding all of the many moving and changing parts is no easy feat. You have a calm, cool demeanor and are doing a great job juggling the priorities and keeping us all informed and on point. Well done you!\n\n107#My testimonial|A big thank you to everyone involved in getting the latest round of testimonials across the finish line. Kevin, you always take the time to review and ensure we’re putting our best foot forward – you provide valuable insight and feedback along the way. Shweta, you did a ton of follow up to secure approvals from our customers, ensuring they felt comfortable and were happy with the final product. Dan, you ensured the new assets were accessible across all of our channels and communicated to our Sales/Marketing teams. Matt F and Jay, I love the look of this latest round. Thank you for combining old footage with new footage, and for making us look good! Angela, thanks for stepping up to ensure this project moved forward in my absence. Matt D, you’ve done an incredible job with the resources page on workhuman.com – thanks for ensuring our testimonials are featured so beautifully. I feel very lucky to work with colleagues I can count on!\n\n108#Dashboard in a Dash|Matt - thanks so much for building the Resource Center dashboard. Your efforts will go a long way in helping our team speak with numbers. You took the time to meet with me, get an understanding of what we'd like to accomplish, and followed up with the Google Analytics configurations we requested. Through your efforts, we can quickly see KPI differences by media type, determining the audience engagement and conversion of blog posts, e-books, papers, podcasts, case studies, webinars, and videos. Not only are you highly skilled, but you approached this with a positive, let's-get-it-done attitude. You are a great teammate. Thank you.\n\n109#The final push aaaaaaaaaaand, we are live!|Matt, the Careers Page is better than I could have imagined and I have YOU to thank for that. You worked tirelessly to ensure our page was not just good, but amazing. We pushed through so many deadlines (or missed them in my case!), to-do lists, copy needs, photography issues, formatting changes, icon designs, more formatting changes, more copy - and so many other things to make our page really shine. We were only *one* small part of the website - but you never minimized or excluded Careers from the level of attention other, larger pages/sections received. I really enjoyed working together and I learned a ton from you on the whole web process and how a new website, truly, is built. Congratulations on an absolutely huge undertaking - you should be incredibly proud not only of the careers page, but the website itself. I am grateful to have had a true partner in this process and am beyond happy with our page. Thank you for everything!\n\n110#Fly Me to the Moon|WOW!!!  Everytime I work with our incredible Creative team, I think I have seen the best, but they always prove me wrong.  Over the past month, all of you have worked so diligently to create a first class experience for our finalist presentation for American Airlines.  Custom boarding passes to be handed out to the meeting attendees.  A 16 page glossy, Globoforce Way magazine for each attendee, which outlined our unique strengths that would satisfy American's needs.  A terric custom demo site, which was being edited up to the night before our presentation.  A beautiful microsite that was used in the pre-RFP phase and then repurposed as a follow-up to thank the American evaluation team.  I cannot thank you enough for all of your creativity, thoughtfulness, support and time.  You are truly the best team ever!\n\n111#Phase II Launch is a Go!|With the Phase II launch of Globoforce.com a success, I can't say enough about your many contributions to the new website. From the very beginning of this redesign you've been a champion for Globoforce, emphasizing the highest quality, keeping the team on schedule, and most importantly managing the relationship with the external agency (the biggest challenge of them all!) During the weeks leading up to the Phase II content launch you were at your best, working many nights and weekends to make sure the site met the high standards we expect at Globoforce. The phenomenal effort you put into this site, and everything you do often goes on behind the scenes, but as always makes a tremendous impact for our Marketing Team and the company as a whole. Great work!\n\n112#A focus on Conversations|While a number of important marketing initiatives have supported Conversations since launch, until recent weeks we haven't had the opportunity or the bandwidth to come together as a team with a cohesive plan to increase awareness, drive demand and better supports the sales and customer success teams. The plan we presented this week is a framework we can build on to better reach the market with a compelling message, and to communicate across marketing and with sales. The planning process got us moving and shines a light on where we need to focus. Thank you all for making the time to contribute with already very full schedules --  a special shout out to Eric B for shepherding the team to get this done!\n\n113#There Wouldn't be Content Without Web|Matt and Brian, Just want to give you both a quick shout out for being amazing partners to the content team. Matt - I come to you quite often (sometimes it seems daily!) for web requests, whether it's a new WorkHuman Radio episode or a request for an update to an asset in the resource center. You're always a pleasure to work with and quick to respond. Brian - you're my go-to for workhuman.com and you're always helpful in answering my many questions on posts, authors, formatting, etc. Just this morning you helped me fix a broken link for a colleague in customer success who wanted to share the post with a customer. Thank you both for your sense of urgency and teamwork in the countless requests and questions I've sent your way over the years!\n\n114#At a moments notice|Matt/Brian- Thank you so much for jumping on the link error for the Oracle microsite. It was needed asap as the conversation was happening in real time and the link was not working. Globoforce looks good because you 2 are behind the scenes. Kudos to you!\n\n115#Mindfulness Matters|While you are spreading your wings into bigger skies (CONGRATS!) you have already been incredible partners during the team transitions. You are thoughtful and caring managers, mindful of your humans and their growth potential. I've thoroughly enjoyed learning from you about each of my newest team members and I look forward to continuing to partner with you to make it at seamless as possible. You've done an incredible job and I hope to build off the solid foundations you already created.\n\n116#URL Hosting Wizard|Matt, thanks so much for your help with registering a URL for me recently. I would have been completely lost with the entire process, and when I reached out you gave great guidance and then took care of it for me in almost no time. The site is going live next week and having an easy-to-remember URL will help our team immensely when socializing it. Thanks again for your help!\n\n117#Bye SnapApp|Matt, thank you for taking the time to research and vet vendors that could better serve our marketing organization. I was so excited to see the potential of a new platform today that would allow us to do more interactive, engaging things for our audiences without the struggle and frustration that is SnapApp. Thanks for including me in the discussion, and I can't wait to see what we are able to do in the future!\n\n118#on call|Thanks for dropping what you were doing to answer a 'call for help' from a meeting room today. Your expertise was needed for an urgent request related to an upcoming SHRM presentation. The time you took to answer a few questions is much appreciated.\n\n119#Employee Experience report ready in record time|Thank you so much for coming together as a team to get the Employee Experience Index ready in time for SHRM. Angela, you spent hours on the phone with Fedex to figure out the most efficient and cost-effective way to print it. Dianne, you quickly mobilized a team, set up kick-off meetings to get the project completed in time. Anthony, Matt and Diane, thank you for your expertise and finding a solution to create a vanity URL on Marketo landing page. Lisa, thanks for your input and for joining the call at such short notice. Alana, thanks for making the slides look pretty. So many slides and so little time. Truly appreciate all your help. Jill, what can I say about you? You are a pleasure to work with. On top of every project, every single time. Thanks, everyone.\n\n120#GPTW Europe 2018!|Thanks to each of you for your help with the announcement of our placement on the Great Place to Work Europe list! From providing input on the employee communication, to sharing pictures from the event, getting the press release out and then on our website, posting on social media, and finally helping get the email out in the Dublin morning hours (while I slept), I'm thankful for the great partnership from everyone on this - all so in sync. Thank you!\n\n121#A Beautiful Mind|When we moved the WorkHuman Radio podcast off of the WordPress site, and onto the new Uberflip site, it created a duplicate of the podcast in the iTunes directory. Should be simple to fix, right? WRONG. Turns out, the old podcast was created with an Apple account almost 8 years ago. Worse, we couldn't get the login to turn it off. I thought we were stuck and I was wrong. You found a workaround within the code that was able to block iTunes from picking up the old feed. You spent so much time on a very frustrating problem, but were able to figure it out! Thank you for your hard work and innovative ideas. You are our John Nash!\n\n122#Action Plans in Action|WorkHuman generates a buzz that gives us an enormous opportunity to follow up with prospects and customers. Each of you went above and beyond to create the Action Plans and breakout session PDFs that were emailed today. Timing was extremely important as we needed to get these out this week for optimal impact. Lauren B and Aaron – thanks for your smart copy. Lauren C, Brian, and Matt – thanks for scrambling to get the session PDFs uploaded in a timely fashion. Amanda – thanks for your wonderful eye for design. Carrie – thanks for providing photos so quickly. Alice and Kevin – thanks for your input and edits. Anthony – thanks for your Marketo expertise to get the emails properly targeted. Jill – thanks for your sales communication. And Lauren C and Amanda – double thanks for scrambling to correct the multiple PDFs that had to be resized at the 11th hour. Crazy week, crazy day – excellent result. Thank you.\n\n123#bigger and better|The gratitude bar was HUGE!!!! And I don't just mean that we made it into a giant screen-tree this year. It was full of humans ALL the time, and people were raving about it. Our attendees were connecting with each other in ways that were so much deeper than the usual chat-over-event-breakfast – all because of the hard work of the people who were dreaming up how to uplevel from last year's experience, testing vertical screens, the mobile interface feed and the curated beautiful loops. Your contributions to the success of this activation cannot be undersold. This is the living, breathing product in the hands of prospects and helps them internalize their own experience of what social recognition can do. It was beautiful and meaningful and I can't thank you all enough for your work on this project!\n\n124#Bringing WHRI Wizardry to Senior Exec Customers!|In the first initiative of its kind in our industry, you helped the WorkHuman Analytics & Research Institute to bring together a session between leading human capital academics and our top HR executive customers.  Elevating the level of conversations we have with our customers is a company-wide goal.  Getting those executive level conversations  and influence points isn't easy.  And - a two hour long event that included Adam Grant and Shawn Achor was no easy feat to pull off during a WorkHuman that included so many tantalizing choices for those executives.  Thank you all for the parts you played - many of them last-minute!  From Kevin helping to open the door with Adam and Ethan, to Lynette and Rebecca being customer recruiting powerhouses, to Stacey and Pam helping with meeting logistics and making sure the group was taken care of, to Matt pushing a last-minute reminder in the WH app so we didn't lose any of these C-level HR execs, to Greg and Chris for working the room with me and making sure customers felt welcome and that we captured next steps with them.  I've heard tons of great feedback from customers on this session and I know this is the beginning of a successful multi-year initiative for Globoforce!  THANK YOU!!\n\n125#Early Birds|Thank you for getting up super early every morning last week before the attendees flooded into WorkHuman Central to reset the LinkedIn survey and rebuild all the charts with me. We could have never made this experience happen without you!\n\n126#WorkHuman Mobile App Help Desk Heroes|It was great working with both of you at the Help Desk at this year's WorkHuman. While our primary function is getting people online and active with the WorkHuman app, you both were ready and willing to jump in to help attendees with any problem, from reviving broken laptops, directing people to specific locations in WorkHuman central, accessing the onsite wireless, or even catching a cab to explore Austin. Great work!!!\n\n127#Masterful Matt!|Matt, somehow you have survived the past 2 weeks—not sure how! Many of you may be thinking of all the shifts at the Help Desk while in Austin, but no, that is just the small tip of a very big iceberg (although thank you for that-- you never left)! You led the development and launch of our WorkHuman app, including troubleshooting unexpected issues with our development partner, resulting in an incredible adoption rate and great experience for all. Then there was the launch of an entirely new website, a huge project in and of itself, but for us also included a new, better host, an entirely new content management engine for our resources center. All of those pieces required tight coordination with legal, marketing ops, our development team and multiple third-party resources. Wow. And at the same time you supported your team in daily updates to Workhuman.com, the launch of the Nashville site, demo sites and probably more than I know. All of these efforts put us on a new level to better deliver our message and reach our market. I look forward to working with you to build on this success! Thank you so much!\n\n128#WorkHuman.com All-Star Team|Thank you all for making WorkHuman.com a success all conference long! Over the course of 4 days we launched 5 separate versions of the site, each with up to date content showcasing the very best of WorkHuman. From our initial strategy meetings weeks ago to the launch of the 2019 Nashville announcement yesterday you have all been amazing teammates who have gone above and beyond to make sure WorkHuman.com and all of its content is a worthy extension of the WorkHuman brand. We're on to 2019!\n\n129#LinkedIn Magicians|Team- Tight turnaround is an understatement. Stats, surveys, graphics, data and the back and forth for literally days...days. I cannot begin to tell you how amazing you’ve all been. Thank you so much for the urgency around everything pertaining to this partnership. It’s going to be awesome!!!\n\n130#Not All Heroes Wear Capes|The week before WorkHuman is always crazy - but this week takes the cake. One of our activations was experiencing some serious technical difficulties, and all of you dropped what you were doing to jump in and make sure we could make it the best it could be. Matt - I can't thank you enough for sitting down with me all morning to design charts and graphs in excel and test their connectivity with PowerPoint. Mark - you came out of nowhere and saved the day with sharepoint magic and a new approach to the survey. Brian & Jen - when we realized our initial solution was a no-go, both of you were quick to offer new ideas and start testing so that we could find the best solution in the least amount of time. And Lee! You jumped up from what you were doing to help us figure out what was causing the disconnect between our local drafts and the live updates. I am SO thankful that we have such an amazing team that was able to take this and run so that our attendees (and our customer!) will have a good experience onsite next week in Austin. THANK YOU!!!!!! You're all amazing.\n\n131#Web Rockstars|Thank you both for your speedy responses with agenda changes to the website and app. There are still changes every day (or every hour) and you update those immediately. This is is a high traffic week and it's key to have the website/app as accurate as possible. You both work until about midnight every night to make it happen. Thank you, we're almost there!\n\n132#Getting everyone the info they need!|Thank you all for your help putting together the WorkHuman staff training material, and for delivering the sessions. It's great when there are many people on a team all contributing to the project - it makes a big lift like this, easy! I really appreciate your attention to the details and for helping make sure employees have all they need to know before traveling to Austin. Thank you!\n\n133#Late Night at the WH Help Desk|Matt! We’re literally in the middle of one of the busiest weeks of the year, especially for the marketing team, and when a customer ran into a snag getting their personal agenda set up with all of the awesome sessions that they plan to attend, you jumped right in with a work around idea. Not only did you get the customer all set up, but you did it in the wee hours, and left a very strategic customer even more excited to get to Austin than they were at the start. Thank you for so clearly demonstrating our culture through your work! Look forward to seeing you at WH!\n\n134#Careers Website! Soft launch - check!|Matt, thank you so much for your incredibly hard work to get the Careers website off the ground before WorkHuman! This was no small feat and I am grateful for your guidance, patience and expertise in this process. I've learned a lot and have really enjoyed working with you. It's exciting to see things come to life and I appreciate all the time, energy and effort you've put in to make sure our page, and every single page, on the new website looks fantastic. I'm excited the soft launch is ready to go and look forward to diving into our next (and final) iteration post WorkHuman!\n\n135#WH App|Matt - I just wanted to recognize all work you have put into the WH App. You've done it so quietly, in the background, without any drama that I'm not sure everyone knows the hours you spent on demos evaluating the choices, the contract process, making sure it could get in the iTunes store with Apple's new policies, loading it up with content and users, and then fixing a LinedIn bug that was discovered to make sure we can use our customer/sponsor's app along in conjunction with ours. Way to go, Matt!\n\n136#Thank you!|Matt, I am so impressed by how quickly you created the American Airlines and Allscripts microsites. You are extremely busy with many other projects and still managed to clone and change out a couple assets to have the site up and running within minutes. This speedy work is helpful so that we can get information in front of prospects quickly. Thank you!\n\n137#Crunch time x 10!|Matt, as you are racing to the finish line on a number of critical projects, I want to give you a shout out for pushing us as a team to up our digital marketing game in a big way. You have long championed our new website- to roll out soon- a huge undertaking to get us to a much better platform to reach our market. At the same time we are launching a new content management platform, and your team is also deeply involved in this little project we call WorkHuman. The WorkHuman app in development (an important part of the conference experience) and the daily demands for web content are another layer that alone would challenge any team. Thank you for the extraordinary effort, and for your leadership on all these fronts!\n\n138#Multiple Microsites|Matt/Kelli- Thank you so much for creating and delivering 5 custom microsites for the Canadian video mailers. Since this was my first experience with these, you sat with me and walked me through these providing documents for sales, 2 different options for sites and creative edits once finished. I appreciate the hand holding and looking forward to seeing the results from these:)\n\n139#In the midst of a storm|Anthony and Matt, great job putting the final touches on our customer communications for the March release notes.  You've been great partners for many years as we have refined our release notes process. For the March communications, you once again showed respect for urgency by quickly responding to my request to publish the notes and make some last minute edits.  And, you did all this in the midst of a massive storm. Thank you.\n\n140#Uberflipping AWESOME!|With a major website upgrade on the horizon and new tools needing to be stood up quickly this team came together to negotiate a contact no one anticipated would be so painful. You all jumped into action to get on calls, make endless contract revisions, and get creative when it came to negotiations. I can't thank you enough for your support. You're all Uberflipping AWESOME!\n\n141#Shouting from the rooftops!|Many thanks to this team for helping share the great news that our Dublin office was named to the 2018 Best Workplaces list in Ireland (for the sixth 