olors and represent Globoforce in the best way possible!\n\n191#Website changes March 20|Matt, with the opening of the new Framingham office brought the need to update the logo on Globoforce.com as well as our address on the Contact Us page. Thank you for taking care of those important details and keeping us looking good online!\n\n192#Linked Careers Page FTW!|Matt, thank you so much for all your help linking our new ATS careers page - and doing it so quickly! I came to you with a very short deadline and you jumped right in, met with the team, obtained necessary approvals, made the changes and spot-checked everything to make sure the functionality was there and the quality was maintained. You saw the big picture and added so much value to the process. The new ATS is a huge step for recruiting and the company and I can't thank you enough for being so willing to dive in to make it happen! We already have candidate applications pouring in! Thanks so much!\n\n193#Once Again, You're the Shining Star|Matt, you have been a great partner to keep our customers informed of our product release notes.  Every few weeks, I come to you with another request to update our customer portal.  You are always more than willing to help out and post our release notes.  For this past request, I sent you a file that exceeded our file size limits.  You painstakingly took the time to reduce the file to a manageable MB size.  I know that was no easy task and I greatly appreciate the time and effort you put into this task.  Thank you for living our respect for customers value and great job responding to this request.\n\n194#Portals and Beyond|Thank you so much for your recent help on several projects that involve updates to the Customer Portal. It is so important to keep the information fresh and relevant and with a rapidly growing Customer Success team, there was a ton of content to be updated! Thank you for fielding my many requests and making them happen in record time. Our customers will appreciate the refreshed info!\n\n195#After-hours coordination|Thank you for the seamless teamwork displayed in coordinating the Great Place to Work Ireland announcement. From finalizing the press release to posting it on Globoforce.com in advance so we could quickly promote the big announcement on social, it was all smooth. And all done well after business hours, with one team member feeling quite under the weather. Thank you for making sure we got everything done together!\n\n196#WorkHuman CHRO Outreach Campaign|Team - THANK YOU all so very much for your fabulous work on the WorkHuman CHRO outreach campaign. AMC and Anthony - amazing support creating 9 lists, Jen and Kelli - impactful designs for online and offline assets, Matt and Brian - quick turnaround on a new site and lots of requested changes, Aaron and Dan - fresh, compelling messages for this executive audience, Jill - setting up a custom CHRO registration experience, Stacey - getting the video of Eric done (and then redone), and of course Dianne for keeping us on track and on task! Great teamwork everyone!\n\n197#Improving WorkHuman Website|Thanks for the quick turnaround with renaming \"News\" to \"Blog\" on the WorkHuman website and getting some fresh posts up so quickly. These moves will help with organic search and set us up for an increased cadence of copy as we ramp toward the conference. Great teamwork and execution.\n\n198#Stepping Up to Make Us Shine!|In recognition of living our value of Urgency!  Matt, you are such a pleasure to work with and always step up to make Globoforce shine in front of our clients.  Last week, out of no where, we received a pretty BIG \"ask\" from one of our newest and largest clients, Schneider Electric.  To help program adoption and reward redemption for the offline population, roughly 40,000  employees, Globoforce is producing 50 Rewards Catalogs featuring gift cards and merchandise available in country by point levels.  And the program manage, Ak, said \"we love the Step Up portal.\"  Can you make this list of changes to the layout of the portal, add a Rewards Catalog category, move other assets around and link all of these catalogs within days so I can share with my HR leadership team at a meeting on Feb 8th.  Ugh!!!  A huge effort, for sure!  And you did all of the heavy lifting, moved things around on your end to accommodate this \"ask\" and in true Matt fashion, kept me in the loop and us, ahead of schedule every step of the way.  I can't thank you enough!!!  The meeting went extremely well and the HR Leadership team is delighted Globoforce has a solution to better support their offline population.  Thanks for Stepping Up and Shining!!!\n\n199#Mindful Meetings - Doing it Right!|I wanted to call out your participation in a wider team meeting we had yesterday.  It was such a great example of doing a meeting right here at Globoforce.  It was collaborative.  It was engaging.  It was open.  You all shared ideas - but also shared concerns about ways we could approach different opportunities - things that could make us more productive.  Questions were asked.  Solutions were brought to the table - with people building ideas off each other.  And it was also fun!  It should be the model for all the meetings we have here.  Great job!\n\n200#WorkHuman App in a Snap!|Matt - Great job in leading our selection process for the WorkHuman app provider.  You were thorough in conducting the search and demos and involving the right people in the process.  Most importantly, you were mindful of our business needs - and ensure that we picked the vendor that was right for us in 2017.  Looking forward to seeing the build out!  Kevin\n\n201#Updates Wizards|Colleen and Matt I would like to thank you for your fantastic, prompt support with the continuous updates I am asking you to make to the careers site and internal signage. I am always impressed at your turnaround times and patience. You are true globostars\n\n202#Kicking off a revolution|When we nee