ing to be amazing! THANK YOU!\n\n210#Perfect Portal Posting!|Matt - Thank you so much for always being so responsive when we need to post content to the Customer Portal.  Whether it's the latest newsletter or Merchant Update, you always get the right information where it needs to be as quickly as possible.  Thank you so much!\n\n211#Marketing Hackathon Success|Thank you for making the first-ever Marketing Hackathon such a success! You embodied all our core values and the results were fantastic. The two-week Marketing sprint made us more agile as a team, brought out new ideas empowering every member of the team, and we found new approaches to market – ideas that could impact both our marketing approach and our go-to market for opportunities ahead. There was a buzz and vibe around the office that was felt by all your enthusiasm and accomplishment - all the way up the executive chain. Simply put, YOU ROCKED IT! Jess, Jill, and Kevin\n\n212#2017 WorkHuman Content!!|Thank you for all of your efforts and urgency to get our WorkHuman agenda draft finalized, speaker outreach started and acceptances, and up on the WorkHuman site. This is a critical step for our marketing efforts and also building out our community. Thank you for your teamwork, thoughtfulness, and dedication to quality!!\n\n213#Matt Step's Up and SHINES!!!!|In recognition of living our Respect for Customers!  Matt, a million thanks for stepping up and setting up the Schneider Electric StepUp Communications Portal!  This huge effort will allow Schneider's internal communication managers/specialists to continuously promote and champion the StepUp program on-going leveraging approved, branded communications in 20  languages.  You did such an amazing job with creating the Abbott comms portal, when we showed Schneider how Abbott comms stakeholders always have ready access to branded comms they said \"WE LOVE THAT. WE WANT THAT.\"  Then last week I hit you with this huge project, asked if I could tap you to help an