emental web piece, and were able to find a variety of options that encompass everything we need to include. I'm definitely looking forward to collaborating with you both on this project, and I can't wait to see how it turns out!\n\n275#Microsite Magic|Thank you so much for jumping in at the last minute to take the Scotiabank microsite to a whole other level. Searching for files, creating new recognition program designs and implementing them into the microsite with such attention to detail is just what we needed to prove to Scotiabank that we're the right recognition partner for them. I appreciate your effort and positivity to make this come to together seamlessly!\n\n276#Patience and Perseverance|Matt, only you and I know how many times I lean around the corner and ask you about our latest website traffic, or for an update on registrations. You deserve an award for putting up with me. But this is not that award. This award is for how remarkable and responsive you have been working on the WorkHuman microsite--in particular from the content point of view. Thank you for being such a great collaborator on how to best to showcase the amazing speakers and sessions we have lined up. And not least for all the times you've let me stand over your shoulder to give you last-minute edits. You truly are the best partner I could ask for. Thank you!\n\n277#Great Collaboration!|I think this award may be slightly overdue but I just want to say a big thank you for all your help with any requests which I have had. Whether it be a last minute change to a job spec that needs to be updated on the career page or the numerous job specs which you add to the page, you are always so prompt with any requests and always so eager to help. I really appreciate it and many thanks for everything! Enjoy!\n\n278#Cvent rockstars|This award is long overdue-but I'm new to the system so sorry about how late it is! I was SO inspired by everyone's willingness to get in a room, roll up the sleeves and stay a bit late to get the job done.  The can-do attitude – especially under pressure – was energizing and I think, in the end, the product showed how dedicated this team is to quality and success! It was a moment that made me realize I could really like it here.\n\n279#Quick problem solver|Matt,     Thanks for taking time between meetings to help me test the link for our new helpdesk tool. Trial and error and a few attempt, but we got it to work. Thanks for dropping what you were doing to help me out.\n\n280#GF New Careers Site|Thank you so much for your time and energy and support in building our new careers site. It looks fab and I can't wait to see it go live shortly. It will make a huge HR difference to us in terms of attracting new talent as it enables us to showcase our employees and what they do, as well as our office space, and that we are a GPTW. It was lovely working with you on this project - it was a true GF team effort!. Enjoy!\n\n281#For the SuperHuman WorkHuman Team|To the fearless and fantastic WorkHuman team,  Thank you, thank you, thank you one and all, for the superhuman efforts you have demonstrated to launch WorkHuman.    The event agenda is positively inspiring, the microsite is flawless, and the promotional campaign is first class.    The behind-the-scenes work required for this launch has been epic, but you have all risen to the challenge, brought your A game, and collaborated to create something truly exceptional.    The weeks ahead will continue to demand this level of individual talent, dogged determination, and energetic collaboration, and I have no doubt that this team will continue to deliver on all fronts.    This is what it’s all about: \"building a work culture that reminds us of our worth as individuals that pulls us together in pursuit of shared goals….\"  Team, you ARE WorkHuman.  Thank you.\n\n282#Web and Systems Master|Hi Matt,  I wanted to thank you for all your effort going above and beyond with Cvent, our Microsite, our website, et