eir respective C&B conferences, so it will get a very wide viewing and I'm sure it will get a huge thumbs up from all who see it. Thanks again guys - enjoy your awards!\n\n303#Great Project Management and Support|Matt,     Thank you so much for your project management and support on the redesign of Recognize This! Blog. This was my first BIG web project, since working at Globoforce, and I know that it came out so well because of the great support and guidance that you gave. It has been great working with you and getting your technical (and sometimes design!) feedback. Also, you also set up a great project plan in Attask (I think it was your first?).     Above all, thank you so much for having faith in me to do a great job. I am very much looking forward to more great projects and work from the team!    :) yay!\n\n304#Marketo Masters|Hi Guys,    I wanted to thank you both for diving in and helping me figure out some back-end code and trouble shoot other ways to work around the system limitations for our registration form. You both had no problem jumping right in and lending a hand after I ran into different road blocks. I really appreciate your help!  Anne Marie\n\n305#Data Driven!|Thank you for quickly gathering the microsite data I needed today, and then some! Your insight helped solidify my gut need to take on the next phase of the project! Thanks again and look forward to taking this project to a new level with you!\n\n306#Ctrl+Alt+Delete|Matt, I know you experienced some difficulties with the Nestle Microsite when updating the URL name and I really appreciate your patience and determination to get it back up and running! THANKS!\n\n307#Shell assets|A huge thanks to you for making Shell a priority. The level of detail, research and thought that went into creating Shell's branded home page, awards, posters, microsite etc...was staggering. Shell were gobsmacked by what you had managed to produce with absolutely no assistance from Shell's own branding people. You guys are creative geniuses! Thanks a mill for helping us create such an impactful first impression.\n\n308#Working together = Success|Henry Ford said - \"Coming together is a beginning.  Keeping together is progress.  Working together is success.\" This quote perfectly captures my sentiments.  We should all be proud of the Service Timelines campaign. We had a large team working together towards a common vision. At times that vision became blurry but we stayed the course and developed a kick butt campaign! We have sent 2 of the email touches and have had 9 companies respond and 2 meetings completed. Extraordinary results from an extraordinary team. Thank you all for your contributions!\n\n309#Web leadership|Matt, I can't thank you enough for your leadership and pro activeness on both upgrading WWW and working with me and the CS team on rapid, radical changes to the customer success site. As we go through our own growth stages, your work to keep our sites working great and engaging visitors is making it easy for everyone to  be successful at Globoforce. Well done!\n\n310#Team Support|I wanted to thank you for all your help with developing assets for the Service Timelines Campaign. You were willing to sit down with me and analyze a plan to move forward. If I had a question or issue, you stepped right in and helped me find a solution. You are a valuable resource and a great teammate. I look forward to working with you on future campaigns and projects. Thanks Matt!\n\n311#SSL certificate|Matt, thank you very much for your help with the www.globoforce.com certificate issue.  This was causing problems with outlook clients poping up message errors. You promptly call the support that host our corporate website to get it sorted asap.  Many thanks again.\n\n312#Blog project management|Thanks for everything you're doing to get the RecognizeThis! blog up to speed in terms of SEO, visibility and adoption. Incorporation more visibly into the website, too, is huge for promoting our thought leadership more broadly. And, of course, thank you for the ongoing project management for the site redesign - keeping all of us (especially me) on track to meet deliverables and deadlines is no easy task and is very much appreciated!\n\n313#Workday page|Great job on getting workday on our website! Prospects will see the level of integration and be impressed!\n\n314#Expanding filespace for secure training|Mark/Alberto/Matt - Many thanks for the quick turn around on expanded HD space on the demo server. Because of your leadership, we can have the confidence that our new training videos for GloboDeck will be secured behind AD-protected authentication. It also means a better usability experience for the people consuming the training. Great work!\n\n315#Awesome Web Ad Results|Matt, I was so impressed to see the transformative changes you made turn in to  AMAZING results for pay-per-click. As a result, our ad costs went down 40% and our ad ratings doubled. Both things improve the results, but also make Google serve our ads more frequently. Awesome work!!\n\n316#Web guru!|Matt, thank you so much for stepping in last week when I needed help with a project that required answering questions about PPC, SEO and retargeting.  It would not have been the same without you there to provide your knowledge. Thank you for the valuable insight and being able to help in such short notice!\n\n317#Radian 6 Integration|Thanks so much for your help with the Radian 6 Salesforce Integration. Your insight in the meeting was integral to the program's success!\n\n318#Thank you for helping me in record time!!|Hi Matt,    A number of people pointed me your way when I needed help to get my microsite done in record time after talking to my prospect last night at 8:30PM; you emailed me back late (which you did not have to do) and put it together in time for the email blast to the HR team @ Lowe today.....it really laid the groundwork for Dave and I to go sell in FL....thank you!!!!\n\n319#Awesome web innovation|Matt, most people in the company I imagine to not see the benefits of your hard work certainly not on a day-to-day basis. Everything you do is incredibly responsive to the field, it's also proactive in terms of getting results. Our site perform better than ever and the company's history, and for the first time this year, they trump all of our competitors in terms of traffic engagement and experience. Great work!\n\n320#Making Abbott's Day - Client Hero|In recognition of living our value of respect for Urgency!  Everyone raise your hands high and give a big, big round of applause to Matt for quickly helping to resolve an issue with one of our largest clients, Abbott, an issue with their Globoforce custom-built communications and training portal website.  The client reached out and mentioned the link for their Excellence program’s communications and training assets re-directed them to a generic globoforce site.  The local program ambassador in Brazil needed to access these materials for an upcoming All Hands meeting.  Anne Marie directed me to you and you were on the case immediately, determining when we switched servers this content did not get migrated.  In less than a day, all of the communications and training assets were re-instated on the new server.  This was no small feat.  The materials are available in English, Brazilian Portuguese, German, Spanish, French, Italian, Japanese, Dutch and Simplified Chinese.  And for each language they have marketing art files, communication templates and a program overview training deck.  On the easy math, that’s 30 assets that were re-instated and ready for use again.  The client is so thrilled with the turnaround, she is sending all of her internal program managers and champions an email reminding them the assets are available and to continue to use them every day to promote and support the program.  That’s fantastic and should result in a spike in activity.  You’re a true Globostar!  Thank you again for all your help and urgency you showed to resolve this matter.  All the best, Traci\n\n321#Great Teamwork|Matt - Thanks so much for meeting with the programs team this week to discuss creative ways that we can integrate our efforts. We look forward to working closely with you to continue to raise the bar with our marketing initiatives.\n\n322#A \"United\" front!|I can't say thank you enough for your \"Respect for Urgency\" in regards to my opportunity with United. Thank you for your incredible turnaround time and sense of urgency.  You are an amazing support to the sales team!\n\n323#Matt Saves the Day (again)!|Hi Matt,  I just wanted to thank you for your help fixing the java script on the Ignite registration pages.  I couldn't for the life of me figure out how it was breaking and you didn't even hesitate to jump in and keep digging until the solution was uncovered.  I can't thank you enough for the help!  Anne Marie\n\n324#To the rescue!|Exceptional job jumping in to help address an issue with the Dow redemption reminder emails. By so quickly updating the GF web page to present well, and allow users to continue on to the Dow site to redeem, this should avoid a large number of users from having access issues and therefore now allow them to redeem.\n\n325#getting it done!|Matt – thank you for all your efforts in getting our emails and landing pages over to Marketo and managing the entire process ever so smoothly. I can’t thank you enough for your diligence and timeliness on this project.  You are always willing to help and take the lead when it comes to our templates. I know how time consuming it can get with some of them, but you do everything you can to get the job done. Thank you!\n\n326#Recognizing the critical|Thanks so much for your help with templates. You recognized the issues, jumped right in and got the job done with a pragmatic and determined attitude. It's great working with someone I can count on to have my back!\n\n327#Support for CSC Project|Thank you for