ed towards a successful launch.  It is such a pleasure working and learning from you! Thanks for your efforts! The company truly benefits from the web expertise and project management you have brought to the table!  ~Anne Marie\n\n338#Herding Cats|Matt - I feel like I would be remiss if I didn't recognize you for the tremendous job you're doing in managing the new website initiative. Your efforts have been herculean, and I really appreciate your clear head and steady hand on the wheel as we close in on the finish line.\n\n339#Pushing the envelope with our new site|Matt, you've know how aggressive our deadlines are for the new site. (they still are) But you've done awesome work to deliver a game changing design. You've put in place to solve our technology issues. And you have kept us all, including me, on track and on plan. Great leadership!\n\n340#Conquering the code!|Matt, I can't thank you enough for your help with the Javascript code on the Event registration page.  I knew I was missing one little piece and your fresh set of eyes looking at the problem brought the perfect perspective and helped me conquer the code.  This will help the team optimize all registrations moving forward for internal events.  Thank you for your Teamwork and Determination!  ~Anne Marie\n\n341#Marketo Solution!|Thank you both for your extra time and assistance reworking the templates for Marketo! You're can do attitude and ability to help at the drop of a hat is the true definition of teamwork!  Thank you!!!\n\n342#Nice work on corporate site updates|Matt - thank you for your patience, flexibility, and help in updating corporate pages on the website.  In the end, it looks great thanks to your continual insight and expertise.\n\n343#Website homepage passed the first round!|The homepage of our website is the face of the company on so many levels. You helped push the envelope on a design that is unique, stunning and a true step forward for Globoforce. Can't wait to see it in development! Keep persevering and taking those risks!\n\n344#New Website|Congrats on your perseverance and leadership on the new site. The design is killer! Very innovative and will really set us apart! Nice work!\n\n345#Job Posting Expert!|Matt I can't thank you enough for all of your help with job postings to the site over the last few months. I know the volume has been high and you are adding and removing jobs daily for us (over 20 so far)! What's more impressive is how quickly the turnaround has been. Thanks again for your part in helping us grow our already amazing team.\n\n346#Quick Turn on the Engage Microsite|Matt,    You were able to move very quickly to create the Engage follow-up microsite. I want to express how great it is to have someone who can make changes to the site -- or build new sites -- quickly and with minimal fuss. It's a huge benefit for the team. Thanks.\n\n347#Speed racer!|Twice in the past few weeks I have come to you with some web related tweaks and both times you have responded immediately and acted within 24 hours. The responsiveness and the changes are much appreciated!\n\n348#Behind the Curtain|Matt - Thanks for taking on your role with such determination and expertise. I really appreciate the knowledge you have brought to us, and the changes you are already putting into effect. I also really appreciate your style, which is both gracious and considerate and also really incisive. I'm really looking forward to what we can all do, together, which I can already see taking shape.\n\n349#Great Web Leadership!|Matt, you've really hit the ground running. I've seen how well you've taken on your new role, evaluated our sites, our vendors, our analytics - everything - to see how we can be the best we can be on the Web. I can't wait to see how we can really up our game in SEO, AB/multi-variant message testing, PPC, etc. under your direction. Nice going!\n\n350#Great first few weeks!|You have done such an amazing job jumping in feet first here at Globoforce, deep